table-0362-596.secondTitle: Common words in Latgalian and Lithuanian, different from Latvian
table-0362-596.caption: Common words in Latgalian and Lithuanian, different from Latvian
data: klausīties in Latvian is "to listen"; klau! means "hey!"
meita in Latvian is used more often as "daughter" while meitene means "girl" exclusively
kleita in Latvian is adapted from the German das Kleid, any native term has been lost
to bathe, to swim in latvian/latgalian to bathe in lithuanian
stulpiņi (diminutive, plural for "stulps") in Latvian is preserved as "leggings"
skaitīt in Latvian means to count, noskaitīt is to recite
atiet in Latvian means to depart (the root word "iet" means "to go")
atsacīt in Latvian means to reject, refuse (and to do it quickly and sharply), atsakyti can be used with this meaning in Lithuanian too
pārsalt in Latvian means to freeze overly (near death)
auksts is more common in Latvian for "cold" than "salts" which is a chilling cold
compound word, in Latvian the order is "leaf"+"side", reverse of the order in Latgalian and Lithuanian
un and ari are common usage in Latvian, "i" is archaic found mainly in folk songs and poetry

"ģimene" is used in Latvian for the core family, saime denotes extended family and household, for example, saimnieks, saimniece are master and mistress, respectively, of the household while in Lithuanian it is giminė which is used for extended family
"rīti" is less common, poetic form in Latvian
"vakari" is less common, poetic form in Latvian
šķēres in Latvian is adapted from the German die Schere, dzirkles refers to shears

table-0362-140.caption: Christmas episode 1989
data: What's Santa Brought for Nora Then?
It's Christmas 1989, and Compo is trying to earn some money to buy Nora a Christmas present. Surely Auntie Wainwright will have something suitable.

50 minute special. Included on the series 11 & 12 boxset. This episode featured (due to popularity the year before) the Second Guest appearance of Auntie Wainwright - whom would later reappear as a regular from 1992 Thereafter This was also the last full episode to feature Seymour Utterthwaite, In the next episode he would only appear briefly. At the end of the episode, one of the presents was a painted egg, presumably a teaser for Foggy's return the following series.

data: Compo and Clegg see Seymour off, ready to take up a post of headmaster. They then just keep missing a returning Foggy.
After a miscommunication leads to Foggy getting split up from Compo and Clegg, while out walking, he comes up with an idea - portable radios.
Compo, Clegg, Foggy, and Howard take part in sponsored football dribble for charity.
Walking Stiff Can Make You Famous
Foggy has come up with another idea, bicycle polo.
After meeting Captain Zero, the human cannonball, the trio take him to the pub while his van is fixed. Unfortunately when he gets arrested for being drunk, it's up to Compo to take his place.
This Episode marks the last appearances of Clegg and Howard's original respective homes.
Foggy decides to restore an old boat, and Compo knows who he wants to take on the first trip...Nora Batty.

From this episode Thereafter, Clegg and Howard move to their new respective homes although still next door neighbours. They would remain there for the rest of the series, until the shows end (20 years later).
The Empire That Foggy Nearly Built
After seeing an argument over a parking space, Foggy decides there must be money to be made out of car parking.
The Last Surviving Maurice Chevalier Impression
Compo impresses a local TV reporter with his Maurice Chevallier impression.
The trio train for a barrel rolling event.
The lads help Smiler find a new place to live.
This Episode marked (due to popularity 2 years before) of Smiler (whom became a regular character from this series onward until 2007).

The girl Yūto already bumped into twice turns out to be Shiina Amamiya, the new transfer student into his class. The school swimming tournament is coming the following week, but while Shiina can do a variety of other skills, swimming is not one of her strong points, so Yūto and Haruka help her prepare in the school pool, but Yūto's sister, and Haruka's sister and maids come along too. At the tournament, Shiina gets a leg cramp during the race and Yūto jumps in to save her, and he takes her to the infirmary. She was not seriously injured, and was more shocked than anything else; Yūto reassures her that she tried her hardest, and that is what matters.

Haruka quickly leaves after seeing Yūto on top of Shiina, but when Yūto tries to explain the situation to her, Haruka says she understands, but ends up running back home. The next day during the school festival, Yūto finds Haruka to have apparently forgotten about yesterday, though Shiina is not so sure. Yūto confronts Haruka about yesterday again, but she tells him she does not want to hear what he has to say and runs off. Yūto runs into Hazuki as he is searching for Haruka, and she gives him some advice on how to move forward with Haruka. With Hazuki's help, Yūto finds Haruka behind the gym where he apologizes for yesterday and assures her that he will not leave her. Afterwards, the two dance by the tune of the music box Yūto gave her previously as Nanami, Mika, and Hazuki watch from the bushes, as the main folk dance, the school festival's culminating event, came to an end minutes earlier.

Mika calls Yūto late at night to invite him to Haruka's birthday party on the evening of October 20. On the day of the celebration, Yūto goes to Akihabara to buy a gift and bumps into Nobunaga, who somehow helps him with choosing the gift. After buying the gift, Yūto goes home and is fetched by Hazuki and Nanami to be taken to the party venue on an island far away together with Ruko and Yukari. On the island, Yūto meets up with Mika and Haruka. After meeting some of the guests, he came across the arrogant rich boy Shute Sutherland, and with his tirades Yūto starts feeling insecure about his gift and social status.

The party has started and Mika drags Yūto inside the party hall. While waiting for Yūto's turn to present his gift, he again bumps into Shute Sutherland and his gift is ridiculed. Yūto becomes insecure and is about to leave the party hall when an old man, who happens to be Haruka’s grandfather, helps Yūto regain back his confidence. Yūto runs back to Haruka and presents his gift. After the party, Yūto is with Haruka in her room, and Yūto then realizes that he was the one who gave the copy of the first issue of Innocent Smile to Haruka when they were kids (well, at Nobunaga's expense). Meanwhile, Shute pays for his insolence when he handled Haruka's grandfather—technically the most powerful person in the castle at the moment—by the collar of his shirt by humiliation from his own father; and was forced to apologize to him and to Yūto in front of a distinguished crowd.

data: "I Made Another Wonderful Memory ♪" "Mata Suteki na Omoide ga Dekimashita ♪" (また素敵な思い出ができました♪)

Yūto and Haruka continue maintain their close relationship, while Shiina’s own feelings for Yūto grow stronger. In preparation for their school trip to Hokkaido, everyone has a reunion at Yūto’s house which soon turns into a party, where afterwards Shiina decides to confess to Yūto during the trip. Once in Hokkaido, Yūto and Haruka spend their free time together, albeit accompanied by Mika, Hazuki, and Nanami who tagged along. At the day’s end, Haruka tells Yūto that she had fun and asks him if they could have another date, to which he happily agrees to. Back at the hotel, Shiina takes Yūto out to the city where she confess that she loves him, which Haruka who had followed them also hears.

At the day’s end, Haruka tells Yūto that she had fun and asks him if they could have another date, to which he happily agrees to. Back at the hotel, Shiina takes Yūto out to the city where she confess that she loves him, which Haruka who had followed them also hears.

Following Shiina’s confession, Yūto is left unsure of how to respond to her, while Haruka is confused on how to interpret her own feelings for Yūto. When Mika, Hazuki, and Nanami learn of her plight, Hazuki tells Haruka they cannot help because Haruka herself must determine how she feels about Yūto. Haruka tries to speak with Yūto, but is unable to do so, and is left in tears when she sees him pulled away by Shiina. After spending the day with Shiina, Yūto comes to realize his feelings for Haruka, and parts ways with Shiina to look for Haruka. When he finds her he confesses his love for her and Haruka reciprocates, and the two officially become a couple, while agreeing to keep their new relationship a secret between themselves. After returning home, Haruka asks Yūto if they can form a doujin circle for the upcoming Summer Comiket, and he agrees to it.

"I Love Anime" "Watashi wa, Anime ga Daisuki desu!" (私は、アニメが大好きです!)

Yūto and Haruka finally completed what they were going to sell at Comiket. Nobunaga then shows up while they were starting up,saying that three girls were looking for their stand. When Yūto and Nobunaga arrive with the three girls,Haruka froze as she saw their faces. The girls were actually her best friends from when she was in middle school. They went there to apologize for turning their backs against Haruka when her secret was revealed back in middle school. They talk things out and Haruka finally forgives them. Later that night,Mika called that her sister was missing. The episode starts with Setsugetsuka Tennōji, who is a rival of Haruka, gloating over being able to hurt Haruka. Yūto decides to go to Haruka and stop her marriage, and is aided by Mika and the maids. His classmates, sister and teacher all join him on the plane to where Haruka is held. Everyone but Yūto and Mika sacrifices themselves to fight the "Hellhounds", while Haruka defeats someone guarding her. Yūto has to fight Haruka's father, while Haruka has to fight her mother to prove their love. They proceed to embrace each other. Haruka's rival steps in, summoning the Tennōji clan's knight, who has already been dealt with by Tōka Tennōji. Haruka and Yūto then get married.

table-0362-5.secondTitle: Relationship between saccadic masking, saccadic movements and motion blur
table-0362-5.caption: Relationship between saccadic masking, saccadic movements and motion blur
data: decision to switch gaze ('look') to behind on the adjacent track
onset of the saccade: angular eye velocity starts rising from 0 deg/s, relative motion of track on the retina starts falling
angular eye velocity rises, and hits 300 deg/s -- that matches the track velocity; the track is resting relative to the retina -- the blur ends
there is no blur on the retina, the saccadic masking is off, snapshot of the image starts to be taken
angular eye velocity is still rising, and exceeds the track velocity; the track starts moving on the retina -- blur resumes
the snapshot starts being processed by the brain, retina 'sees' only the blur now
the image has been processed and one becomes aware of it: one sees the image; at this time the saccade could have already finished.

Yūto and Haruka begin making a dōjinshi together, though Haruka's skill in drawing is still lacking. Nobunaga asks Yūto to cover for him selling dōjinshi for one of his friends' dōjin circles at an upcoming event for Nocturne Girl's School Lacrosse Club. Yūto asks Haruka to accompany him, who is overjoyed at the prospect of helping out an already established circle. Yūto and Haruka continue their work on Haruka's illustration book of the Nocturne Girl's School Lacrosse Club lead character Haruna, though the day of the event Haruka's book is not selling. Nobunaga gives Yūto some advice, telling him that half the enjoyment is actually making the dōjinshi and Yūto realizes there are more important things that the book selling or not. Yūto goes back to Haruka and starts promoting Haruka's book, and eventually three people end up buying it.

After finding out that Haruka is working to get him a Christmas present, Yūto decides to apply for a well-paying job as a part-time butler. He gets the job, but he must serve the selfish and demanding Tōka Tennōji, a schoolmate of his one year his junior, whose previous part-time butlers quit after a day or less under her command. Yūto does his best to satisfy Tōka's requests, though she is still largely unsatisfied with this efforts. Yūto learns that Tōka's family is currently undergoing negotiations of inheritance after her grandfather died, which is having an adverse effect on Tōka's emotional state. Through kindness and hard work, Yūto manages to gain Tōka's favor, but after his older sister and homeroom teacher invade the Tennōji mansion (which involves attacking and hurting the security guards and doing related damage), nearly all of Yūto's pay is taken in order to repair the costs.

"Yūto's Scent..." "Yūto-san no Nioi..." (裕人さんのにおい...)

The Nogizaka family visits Yūto's house for a Christmas party. However, the party is cut short when Yūto faints since he overworked himself to exhaustion to buy Haruka a Christmas present. When Yūto regains consciousness, Haruka declares that she will stay by his side in order to nurse him back to health, under the guidance of a questionable guidebook that Mika prepared. To preserve the Christmas spirit in spite of Yūto's poor health, Haruka decorates his yard with Christmas lights, and presents him with a necklace with a golden charm as Christmas present. He in turn presents her with his present: a ring (called the Moonlight) which, at Haruka's request, he places on her ring finger. Mika and the crew accentuated the moment by making some artificial snow at the rooftop.

Yūto is invited to the annual encounter of maids and butlers due to his one week job at the Tennōji household. Yūto is introduced to the rest of the Nogizaka family's maids and enjoys the party alongside Alice, until the arrival of Shute Sutherland, the same rich boy who caused him trouble during Haruka's birthday party, who was ordered by his father to work as a butler for a while as a lesson in humility. After having his suit accidentally dirtied by Alice, Shute shouts at her and steps on the toy Yūto gave her; and states how the butlers and maids at the party are inferior beings. However, Yūto stands to protect Alice, and, with Shute's father's approval (he heard it all on the phone), he and his lackeys are given the proper punishment by the members of the gathering. Yūto is complimented by the other guests, and Alice mutters some words of thanks to him.

Yūto visits Mika's junior high school—an all-girls school—upon her invitation. Mika introduces him to the rest of the girls in her class. He was surprised to know that Mika was a popular girl at school. She is a class president and a school idol, pretty much like her sister Haruka. After their meeting, Yūto decides to go and see Mika's stage play. After the stage play, both Yūto and Mika are accidentally locked up in the stage room. Luckily in the end, Mika's maids find them.

"This is My First Experience ☆" "Hatsutaiken desu ☆" (初体験です☆)

Haruka and Yūto are finally having some time for themselves. They go to the fair to have some fun together. There, Milan Himemiya's managers, Yayoi Kayahara and Nozomi Kobayakawa, get Yūto and Haruka to take a picture together. That night, they have a ride on the Ferris wheel and confirm their relationship, though not without the hijinks caused by a quite shaky Ferris wheel. Haruka's picture is taken to capture the moment. Yayoi and Nozomi then formally embarks on their real agenda for Haruka: grooming her into an idol.

Haruka agrees to attend the audition for Yayoi and Nozomi. Yūto waits as Haruka gets ready for the audition, and is told by Yayoi not to interfere. While waiting, Yūto once again bumps into the girl he met before at the shrine, who turns out to be the idol Milan Himemiya. Milan decides she wants Yūto as her manager since her own manager is currently in a different prefecture. Yūto and Milan go around together to photo shoots, voice acting and other things. After his work as a manager, Yūto overhears Yayoi and Nozomi while poring over Haruka's photographs. It becomes clear to him that the talent agency actually wants Haruka to become an idol—something of which Milan had tipped him off earlier.

Yūto is invited to come with the Nogizakas to a ski resort in the mountains. He thinks it is just for them but he quickly finds out the entire class is coming on this trip. While the group enjoys all the hot spring resort has to offer, Shiina sees the trip as an opportunity to express her feelings to Yūto—but in an attempt to hug him, she ends up groping Gento, who was covered in sheets. An enraged Akiho catches them in a compromising position and gets the wrong idea, causing Gento to pass on the group's shrine visitation the next day. The next evening, a blizzard arrives and Haruka goes missing on the top of the mountain. When Yūto, equipped with an insulated polar bear suit, finds her, they both fall down a ridge and become stuck in a cabin. As she is wet and freezing, Haruka takes off her clothes and joins Yūto in his bear suit in just her underwear. However, the two are quickly found not only because the bear suit has a tracking device, but also because the cabin turns out to be just behind the resort.
